# Manual fallback regex strings for mods that cannot auto-generate a unique regex.
# Format:  modIndex=fallbackString
# The fallbackString is used verbatim as the regex token when no substring match can be found.
# Find the mod index from the sanity check console.table() output at startup.
#
# Example:
# 33=Rare Mo
# 34=more Mo
#% more Monster Damage=% m.*ge$
#% increased Monster Damage=% i.*ge$
Monsters gain an Endurance Charge on Hit=n e.+t$
Natural inhabitants of this area have been removed\nArea is infested with Fungal Growths\nMap's Item Quantity Modifiers also affect Blight Chest count at #% value\nCan be Anointed up to # times=wt
Natural inhabitants of this area have been removed\nArea is infested with Fungal Growths\nMap's Item Quantity Modifiers also affect Blight Chest count at #% value\nCan be Anointed up to # times\n#% increased Monster Movement Speed\n#% more Monster Life\nMonster Level: #=wt
Monsters cannot be Stunned\n#% more Monster Life=unn
#% increased Monster Movement Speed\n#% increased Monster Attack Speed\n#% increased Monster Cast Speed=r at
#% increased Monster Cast Speed\n#% increased Monster Attack Speed\n#% increased Monster Movement Speed=r at
Players are Cursed with Vulnerability\nPlayers are Cursed with Temporal Chains\nPlayers are Cursed with Elemental Weakness=h v|h el|h tem